<item>
            <title>[CXF-7687] AuthorizationPolicy: AuthorizationType=&quot;Bearer&quot; has no effect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7687</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Adding an AuthorizationPolicy object with&#160;AuthorizationType set to &quot;Bearer&quot; to the Client HTTPConduit object has no effect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No &quot;Authorization: Bearer xxx&quot; header is added to the cxf request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround: add the Authorization header directly:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;client.getRequestContext().put(Message.PROTOCOL_HEADERS, authorizationHeader);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and authorizationHeader containing the desired header/value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
